{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-add-top-link-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Add Top Link in Magento 2Â ","content":"\n<p><strong>Adding top link in Magento 2</strong> is all we will learn today to improve the user experience Magento 2 is a popular e-commerce platform that offers advanced features and tools to create a professional and customized online store. With Magento 2, you can easily design a visually appealing and user-friendly website that caters to your business and customers&#8217; specific needs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the critical components of any e-commerce website is the top links menu, which enables customers to navigate to essential pages like the shopping cart, account login, and wishlist quickly. Typically located at the top of the page, this menu provides easy access to key areas of your website and helps customers find what they need quickly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Magento 2 provides an intuitive interface to <a href=\"https://meetanshi.com/blog/add-top-link-in-magento-2/#:~:text=The%20top%20links%20must%20be,user%20experience%20and%20sales%20boost.\" class=\"ek-link\">add top links to your website</a>, including the ability to <a href=\"/how-to-add-dynamic-links-to-the-footer-in-magento-2/\">add a Dynamic Link to Footer</a>. You can customize the top links menu to include links to pages that are relevant to your business, such as product categories, promotions, or customer service.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By adding top links to your Magento 2 website, you can significantly improve the user experience of your online store, making it easier for customers to navigate and find what they are looking for. This can ultimately lead to increased sales and customer loyalty as customers are more likely to return to a website that provides a seamless and hassle-free shopping experience. This blog post will guide you through the process of <strong><em>how to add top link in Magento 2.</em></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Method to add Top link Magento 2&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>First Go to <strong>app/code/Vendor/Extension/view/frontend/layout/default.xml</strong> and paste the below Given code.</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;page xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation=\"urn:magento:framework:View/Layout/etc/page_configuration.xsd\"&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;body&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;referenceBlock name=\"header.links\"&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;!-- Contact us Link --&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;block class=\"Magento\\Framework\\View\\Element\\Html\\Link\" name=\"contactus.link\" after=\"register-link\"&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;arguments&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;argument name=\"label\" xsi:type=\"string\" translate=\"false\"&gt;Constact Us&lt;/argument&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;argument name=\"path\" xsi:type=\"string\" translate=\"false\"&gt;contact-us&lt;/argument&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/arguments&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/block&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;!-- CMS Page Link Link --&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;block class=\"Magento\\Framework\\View\\Element\\Html\\Link\" name=\"aboutus.link\" after=\"contactus.link\"&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;arguments&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;argument name=\"label\" xsi:type=\"string\" translate=\"false\"&gt;about Us&lt;/argument&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;argument name=\"path\" xsi:type=\"string\" translate=\"false\"&gt;about-us&lt;/argument&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/arguments&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/block&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/referenceBlock&gt;\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/body&gt;\n\n&lt;/page&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To summarize, incorporating top links into your Magento 2 website is a straightforward procedure that can significantly improve the user experience of your e-commerce store. By adhering to the instructions provided in this blog post, you can readily personalize the top links menu to cater to the demands of your business and customers.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-add-top-link-in-magento-2/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-al